def add_num(a, b):
    """""
    this function take the input / numeric input ..2 numeric input and add them
    and store the result in the result variable
    
    result is a global variable
    """""
    print("value of a is", a)
    print("value of b is", b)
    global result
    result = a + b 
    print("the result is", result)

def remove_outliers(df,col,k=2):   
    mean = df[col].mean()  # calculating the mean
    length1  = df.shape[0]
    global df1
    sd = df[col].std()   #  cal the DTD   
    final_list = [x for x in df[col] if (x > mean - k * sd)]
    final_list = [x for x in final_list if (x < mean + k * sd)]       

    df1 = df.loc[df[col].isin(final_list)] ; print(df1.shape) ; length2 = df1.shape[0]
    tot = length1 - length2
    print("number of outliers removed are -->" ,tot)       
    
       # in k means standard deviation . 
        # increse the value of k, outlier will be decreses .
